window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>An instant classic, Brian Lumley's astonishing feat of imagination spawned a universe that Lumley has explored and expanded through more than a baker's dozen novels and novellas. Millions of copies of <i>Necroscope</i> and its successors are in print in a dozen languages throughout the world. Nominated for the British Fantasy Award, <i>Necroscope</i> has inspired everything from comic books and graphic novels to sculptures and soundtracks. This new edition of <i>Necroscope</i> uses the author's preferred text and includes a special introduction by Brian Lumley, telling how the Necroscope saga came to be. </p> <p>Harry Keogh is the man who can talk to the dead, the man for whom every grave willingly gives up its secrets, the one man who knows how to travel effortlessly through time and space to destroy the vampires that threaten all of humanity. </p>"; 
